      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DURAN QUEEN (4) was well in the market last time but only managed fourth (23.89), beaten 7 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Better than last start and worth following up. KEY AURORA (1) turned in a moderate effort last time when seventh at this track over 400m behind Hello Chevy (23.50) in a Grade 5. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can do much better this time. WELL KNOWN (2) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 7 length second (25.59) in a Grade 5 at Gunnedah. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Leading chance. POWER ROLEX (8) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
